\par 
\par 50th and 51-st Divisions: The return of members of the 50th and 51stDivisions is causing comment and many believe they are to be the spear-head in the invasion of Western Europe (Four Regions). Some consider they have had enough fighting and}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16209235  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16209235 should not be sent abroad
\par again.
\par 
\par Forces' mail. Two reports refer to parcels from men in the Forces abroad being tempered with.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16209235  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16209235 
One refers to "organised thieving" from parcels from the Middle East, many of which fail to arrive intact - "food parcels often do not arrive at all". It is suggested that the contents list should be erased after censorship, as this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16209235  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16209235 particularly when it mentions silk stockings is a temptation, Some concern is also expresse
d by the public on learning of the "non-arrival of parcels sent to the men out East''. One case is alleged where seventeen parcels were sent, not one of which was received.
\par 
\par R.A.F.: Some concern is expressed (Three Regions) at the alleged loss of pay and rank" incurred when}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16209235  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16209235 
men are grounded through circumstances beyond their control. This is thought unfair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9123155 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16209235 (1.2.3.5.6.7.10.11)
